parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the motorcycle to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: The motorcycle stalls or fails to start
the motorcycle loses power while in operation
the ignition switch fails to turn off
the motorcycle requires repeated attempts to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear ABS can cause the rear wheel to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and increased stopping distances, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear anti-lock brakes stop working
the rear wheel locks up during emergency braking
the ABS system is no longer functional.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden release of fuel from the tank can cause serious personal injury, property damage, and potentially lead to fires or explosions.
symptoms: Fuel spews out of the tank when the fuel cap is opened
covering the surrounding area and potentially causing damage to the vehicle and nearby objects.
